Starbucks says a computer outage affected registers at 8,000 stores in the US and Canada . 
  The global coffeehouse chain says stores are expected to open for 'business as usual' Saturday . 
  Earlier the company said the outage affected 7,000 US stores and 1,000 in Canada . 
  It prompted baristas to give away free drinks and baked goods . 
  The outage began in the early evening on the East Coast and in the late afternoon on the West . 
 